Apa puncannya?

The higher the inflation rate (the price of the goods) the less the power of our purchase. If we used to buy 1 egg, today we need 40 cents for the same egg.

What's the point?

It's a reality. I have a little experience in SMEs from a young age (now young), I can talk a little bit.

Text:
APA ITU INFLASI?

Kenaikan harga barang dan servis dalam ekonomi kita. Kalau dulu kita beli nasi lemak 60 sen sebungkus. Sekarang dah jadi RM1.80 sebungkus. 

Keburukannya ialah nilai matawang kita semakin kecil.
Translated_Tweets:
What is inflation?

The increase in prices of goods and services in our economy. If we used to buy 60 cents fat rice. It's been RM1.80 now.

The disadvantage is that our currency value is smaller.

Text: Dari segi teori ekonomi, perkara asas yang menentukan harga barang ialah bekalan dan permintaan. Jika permintaan meningkat dan bekalan meningkat sama, harga akan bertahan. Jika bekalan berkurangan tetapi permintaan tetap tinggi, harga akan naik.
Translated_Tweets: In terms of economic theory, the basic factors that determine the price of goods are supply and demand. If demand increases and supply increases, prices will survive. If the supply decreases but the demand remains high, the price will rise.
